{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-85d833b320c553e4", "type": "tool_result", "content": "1\t                                            Diarization-Guided Qwen-ASR Adaptation for Multilingual Two-Speaker\n2\t                                                                   Conversational Speech\n3\t                                                                   Hao Wu1,∗ , RongQi Han1,∗ , Zhen Wang1 , Wei Liang2 , Wei Xu1\n4\t                                                                               1\n5\t                                                                                   Shanghai Qi Zhi Institute, Shanghai, China\n6\t                                                                                2\n7\t                                                                                   Megatronix (Beijing) Technology Co., Ltd\n8\t                                                                                                   wuhao@sqz.ac.cn\n9\t\n10\t\n11\t                                                                  Abstract                                   minimized over speaker permutations under time constraints,\n12\t                                                                                                             with diarization quality reported separately through the diariza-\n13\t                                        This paper describes our self-designed system for Task 1 of the      tion error rate (DER). The 2026 Task 1 setting is deﬁned by the\n14\t                                        MLC-SLM 2026 Challenge for multilingual two-speaker con-             ofﬁcial challenge page as multilingual conversational speech di-\n15\t                                        versational speech. The system combines a modular speaker di-        arization and recognition [1].\n16\t                                        arization front end with a challenge-adapted Qwen3-ASR-1.